============================================================================================================================================
READING THIS
============================================================================================================================================
• POOLED = upper bound. Stakes sized off TOTAL bankroll, zero transfer friction.
• SILO   = lower bound. Stakes sized off each provider's own balance, no transfers ever.
• HYBRID = the regime we actually run. Unlimited pooled (Pinnacle/Cloudbet/Kalshi/Polymarket)
           as one balance, softs siloed for sizing, profit above starting arbs to unlimited.
• 'drain' = median $ arbed from softs → unlimited over the 180-day run.
• 'arb / start' = drain expressed as fraction of starting TOTAL bankroll.
• 'S→H saved' = days hybrid saves vs pure silo on time-to-2x.
